The importance of the horse in the colonial and Native American cultures is of utmost importance. Native Americans did not have the wheel until Europeans arrived. I doubt there is any way to overestimate the importance of the Columbian Exchange in terms of an expansion of biological diversity. On the other hand, as Akannan points out, the exchange of ideas and ideals is equally important.
